Scope – Storage Assessment 		
4.1	Overview
The Teleperformance India is running their entire IT Landscape On-premises and Co-located in Third party Datacenter, the existing hardware is End Of Life / End Of Support / Annual Maintenance Contract (AMC) contract is at renewal stage, due to which Teleperformance India is looking for assessment of entire IT landscape and Storage, after the successful assessment of IT Infrastructure they are planning to migrate entire setup on Cloud. 
•	Objective: 
Clearly outline the goals and objectives of the storage assessment.
Define the scope of the assessment, including the systems, applications, and data to be evaluated.
•	IT Landscape / Storage Assessment Plan 
Storage assessment plan involves a systematic approach to evaluating current multiple storage and IT infrastructure, identifying requirements, and strategizing improvements. Below is the structured for a storage assessment plan:
Define the specific requirements and objectives of moving storage with the cloud, consider factors like data volume, access patterns, performance needs, compliance, and budget constraints.
Compatibility with Cloud Services: Assess if the Dell / HP storage solution is compatible with the targeted cloud service provider (CSP) or cloud model (public, private, and hybrid). Verify support for APIs, protocols, and data transfer mechanisms required by the chosen cloud environment.
Scalability and Flexibility: Evaluate the scalability features of the Dell / HP storage solution. Check if it allows for easy scaling to accommodate growing data needs and if it supports different storage tiers or performance levels that align with cloud requirements.
•	Conduct a comprehensive evaluation of the customer's current on-premises infrastructure.
•	Formulate a tailored cloud migration strategy aimed at optimizing cost, performance, and scalability. This includes estimating the technical efforts required for migration.
•	Define the migration process and identify the necessary technologies and tools for a seamless transition.
•	Specify the data migration process, including options such as Lift & Shift, utilizing services like
•	Azure Data Box Heavy or Data Box Gateway, Tape-Based / Backup Based (Lift & Shift), or third-party tools over the WAN.
•	Explore bandwidth capacity design based on data size.
•	Consider using WAN Technology, Dedicated IIL, or P2P Link for migration.
•	Evaluate options like Site-to-Site VPN or IPsec VPN tunnels.
•	Define the required resources and man-hours for the migration team.
•	Gain a thorough understanding of the source system's operating system, databases, network, security, access, and control mechanisms.
•	Assess whether any operating system or database-level upgrades/updates are necessary.
•	Consider End-of-Life (EOL) and End-of-Support (EOS) status from the Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM).
•	Continue refining the customized cloud migration strategy to ensure ongoing optimization of cost, performance, and scalability.

